headlines.description: — Keaton Wallace posted his first career triple-double and Atlanta beat the Orlando Magic 117-105 on Sunday to give the Hawks a split of their four-game, regular-season series and momentum for a rematch in the play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keaton Wallace logs first career triple-double as Hawks beat Magic 117-105 before play-in rematch

headlines.description: — Payton Pritchard scored 34 points on Sunday and the Boston Celtics swept consecutive home games against the Charlotte Hornets with a 93-86 victory despite blowing a 21-point first-half lead in a regular-season ending matchup of all reserves.
headlines.shortLinkText: Payton Pritchard scores 34 points in Celtics' 93-86 regular-season ending victory over Hornets

events.name: New York Knicks at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Landry Shamet scored a season-high 29 points, playing starter's minutes after replacing Mikal Bridges just 6 seconds into the game, and the New York Knicks beat the Brooklyn Nets 113-105 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Landry Shamet scores 29 after replacing Bridges after 6 seconds, leads Knicks past Nets 113-105

headlines.description: — Quenton Jackson scored 21 points, RayJ Dennis had seven points in the second overtime and the Indiana Pacers rallied for a 126-118 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Sunday after trailing by 23 with 7:35 remaining in regulation.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers rally from 23-point deficit in 4th quarter to defeat Cavaliers 126-118 in double overtime

headlines.description: — Tristan Vukcevic had 28 points and 11 rebounds, Justin Champagnie added 27 points and Bub Carrington banked in a game-winner as time expired to put the Washington Wizards over the Miami Heat 119-118 on Sunday in both teams' regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bub Carrington hits game-winner as time expires to lift Wizards past play-in bound Heat 119-118

headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter hit five 3-pointers and scored 18 points and the Chicago Bulls warmed-up for the play-in game with a 122-102 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls get ready for NBA play-in game with 122-102 win over 76ers in regular-season finale

headlines.description: — Pat Connaughton had a career-high 43 points and a season-high 11 rebounds as the Milwaukee Bucks defeated the Detroit Pistons 140-133 in overtime on Sunday to close the regular season on an eight-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Connaughton has career-high 43 points as Bucks beat Pistons 140-133 in OT to close regular season

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. scored 19 points, Aaron Gordon and Nikola Jokic added 18 each and the Denver Nuggets clinched the No. 4 seed in the Western Conference with a 126-111 win over the Houston Rockets on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets secure No. 4 seed in Western Conference with 126-111 rout of Rockets

headlines.description: — Lamar Stevens scored a career-high 31 points, Marvin Bagley III had 25 points and 11 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the Dallas Mavericks 132-97 on Sunday in the teams' regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar Stevens scores career-high 31 points as Grizzlies coast to a 132-97 win over Mavericks

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 18 of his 43 points in the third quarter to help the Minnesota Timberwolves pull away from the Utah Jazz for a 116-105...
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves secure playoff spot with 116-105 win over Jazz behind 43 points from Anthony Edwards

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: - Rookie center Branden Carlson scored a season-high 26 points to go with 10 rebounds and three blocked three shots, and the Oklahoma City Thunder wrapped up the best regular season in franchise history with a 115-100 victory over the injury-depleted...
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins and Carlson lift Thunder past Pelicans 115-100 in regular-season finale

events.name: Toronto Raptors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson had 23 points, Stephon Castle added 20, and the San Antonio Spurs rallied from a 22-point deficit to beat the Toronto Raptors 125-118 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs rally from a 22-point deficit to beat the Raptors 125-118

events.name: LA Clippers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — James Harden hit consecutive 3-pointers in overtime, a pair of free throws and scored on Jimmy Butler’s goaltending to finish with 39 points and 10 assists, Kawhi Leonard added 33 points, and the Los Angeles Clippers secured the fifth seed in the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Leonard lead Clippers past Warriors 124-119 in OT to secure fifth seed in West playoffs

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Dalano Banton scored 23 points and the Portland Trail Blazers ended their season Sunday with a 109-81 victory over the playoff-bound Los Angeles Lakers, playing without Luka Doncic and LeBron James.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers end season with 109-81 win over short-handed playoff-bound Lakers

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis and Jonas Valanciunas each had a double-double, and Sacramento clinched homecourt advantage for the Kings first play-in game, beating the Phoenix Suns 109-98 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis, Valanciunas lead Kings past Suns in finale
